						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the well in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Baṅkidēva, 1286 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record seems to register a gift of land on the occasion of a solar eclipse, to god Gōpināthadēva.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[20]9, Vyaya, Mārgaśira śu. 10, Vaḍḍavāra.</hi> The details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1286 A.D., November 26, Tuesday, f.d.t. ·30.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
